    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomatoey-pollock-and-caper-stew-with-couscous-and-mixed-seeds/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Chop your<strong> tomato[es] </strong>roughly</p><p>Deseed your <strong>sweet pointed pepper[s] </strong>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop roughly</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomatoey-pollock-and-caper-stew-with-couscous-and-mixed-seeds/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped sweet pointed pepper </strong>and <strong>tomato</strong> to the<strong> </strong>pan with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to soften</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomatoey-pollock-and-caper-stew-with-couscous-and-mixed-seeds/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>couscous</strong> to a heatproof bowl with <strong>half</strong> your <strong>dried oregano </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and 100ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [150ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Stir together, then cover and set aside \u2013 this is your <strong>herby couscous</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomatoey-pollock-and-caper-stew-with-couscous-and-mixed-seeds/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pepper is starting to soften, add the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> to the pan with your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>dried</strong> <strong>oregano</strong> and <strong>capers</strong></p><p>Cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomatoey-pollock-and-caper-stew-with-couscous-and-mixed-seeds/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> to the pan with 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span><span class=\"text-purple\"> </span><strong>boiled water</strong> and stir it all together</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomatoey-pollock-and-caper-stew-with-couscous-and-mixed-seeds/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> diced pollock </strong>(unevenly sized diced pollock? Chop any larger ones into bite-sized pieces!) to the stew<strong> </strong>and and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce heat to medium and cook for 4-5 min further or until the fish is cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>Sicilian-style pollock stew</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomatoey-pollock-and-caper-stew-with-couscous-and-mixed-seeds/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Sicilian-style pollock stew </strong>with the<strong> herby couscous </strong>to the side</p><p>Top with your <strong>pine kernel & seed mix</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
